sequenceDiagram
    participant User as Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard as ODH Dashboard
    participant K8sAPI as K8s API Server
    participant RhodsOp as rhods-operator
    participant KServeCtrl as KServe Controller
    participant Knative as Knative Serving
    participant ODHModelCtrl as odh-model-controller
    participant AuthorinoSvc as Authorino
    participant S3 as S3 Storage
    participant ISVCPod as ISVC Pod
    participant TrustyAISvc as TrustyAI
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as OpenShift Route

    Note over User,Client: Workflow 1: Model Serving (KServe Serverless)

    User->>Dashboard: Login via OpenShift OAuth
    Dashboard-->>User: Show Data Science Projects
    User->>Dashboard: Create InferenceService via UI
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: POST InferenceService CR<br/>(Bearer token passthrough)

    K8sAPI->>RhodsOp: Webhook: mutate ISVC<br/>(HardwareProfile GPU injection)
    RhodsOp-->>K8sAPI: Mutated ISVC with resources

    K8sAPI->>KServeCtrl: Watch: new InferenceService
    KServeCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create Knative Service<br/>(autoscaling config)
    K8sAPI->>Knative: Reconcile Knative Service
    Knative->>K8sAPI: Create Pod with revision

    K8sAPI->>KServeCtrl: Webhook: mutate Pod
    Note over KServeCtrl: Inject storage-initializer<br/>init container +<br/>kserve-agent sidecar

    K8sAPI->>ISVCPod: Start init container
    ISVCPod->>S3: Download model artifacts<br/>(HTTPS/443, AWS IAM)
    Note over ISVCPod: Model loaded, runtime ready

    K8sAPI->>ODHModelCtrl: Watch: InferenceService ready
    ODHModelCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create Route + NetworkPolicy
    ODHModelCtrl->>K8sAPI: Create ServiceMonitor
    ODHModelCtrl->>AuthorinoSvc: Create AuthConfig<br/>(if mesh enabled)

    K8sAPI->>TrustyAISvc: Watch: ISVC (if TrustyAI enabled)
    TrustyAISvc->>K8sAPI: Patch ISVC with<br/>payload logging sidecar

    Note over Gateway,ISVCPod: Model endpoint ready for inference
    Client->>Gateway: POST predict<br/>(HTTPS/443, TLS)
    Gateway->>ISVCPod: Forward request<br/>(mTLS if mesh enabled)
    ISVCPod-->>Gateway: Prediction result
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON response (HTTPS)

    User->>Dashboard: View model metrics
    Dashboard->>K8sAPI: Query ISVC status + metrics
    Dashboard-->>User: Model health + latency

%% --- Workflow 2 separator ---

sequenceDiagram
    participant User2 as Data Scientist
    participant KServeCtrl2 as KServe Controller
    participant K8sAPI2 as K8s API Server
    participant GatewayAPI as Gateway API
    participant Envoy as Envoy Gateway
    participant EPP as llm-d EPP
    participant KVCache as llm-d KV-Cache
    participant DecodePod as Decode Worker (vLLM)
    participant PrefillPod as Prefill Worker (vLLM)
    participant RoutingSidecar as Routing Sidecar
    participant Client2 as External Client

    Note over User2,Client2: Workflow 2: LLM Inference (Disaggregated P/D via llm-d) [New in 2.25]

    User2->>K8sAPI2: Create LLMInferenceService CR
    K8sAPI2->>KServeCtrl2: Watch: new LLMInferenceService

    KServeCtrl2->>K8sAPI2: Create InferencePool
    KServeCtrl2->>K8sAPI2: Create InferenceModel
    KServeCtrl2->>K8sAPI2: Create Deployments<br/>(prefill + decode workers)
    KServeCtrl2->>K8sAPI2: Create Gateway HTTPRoute
    KServeCtrl2->>K8sAPI2: Create EPP StatefulSet

    Note over EPP: EPP connects to pods via<br/>ZMQ for KV-cache events

    EPP->>KVCache: Subscribe to KV-cache<br/>state updates (ZMQ)

    Client2->>Envoy: POST /v1/chat/completions<br/>(HTTPS/443)
    Envoy->>EPP: ext-proc gRPC call<br/>(select backend)

    Note over EPP: Plugin pipeline:<br/>1. Filter by role labels<br/>2. Score by KV-cache prefix<br/>3. Score by load<br/>4. Select optimal pod

    alt Cache hit on decode pod
        EPP-->>Envoy: Route to decode pod<br/>(direct)
        Envoy->>DecodePod: Forward request
        DecodePod-->>Client2: Stream response
    else Cache miss - P/D split needed
        EPP-->>Envoy: Route to decode pod +<br/>x-prefiller-host-port header
        Envoy->>DecodePod: Forward request
        DecodePod->>RoutingSidecar: Intercept request
        RoutingSidecar->>PrefillPod: Forward to prefiller<br/>(NIXL v2 protocol)
        PrefillPod->>PrefillPod: Compute KV-cache blocks
        PrefillPod->>DecodePod: Transfer KV-cache<br/>(RDMA/NIXL)
        DecodePod->>DecodePod: Decode with transferred cache
        DecodePod-->>Client2: Stream response (SSE)
    end

%% --- Workflow 3 separator ---

sequenceDiagram
    participant User3 as Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard3 as ODH Dashboard
    participant DSPAPI as DSP API Server
    participant MariaDB as MariaDB
    participant ArgoCtrl as Argo Controller
    participant DriverPod as DSP Driver
    participant LauncherPod as DSP Launcher
    participant MLMD as ML Metadata
    participant PersistAgent as Persistence Agent
    participant S3_3 as S3 Storage

    Note over User3,S3_3: Workflow 3: ML Pipeline Execution

    User3->>Dashboard3: Create pipeline run via UI
    Dashboard3->>DSPAPI: Submit pipeline run<br/>(Bearer token passthrough)

    DSPAPI->>MariaDB: Validate + store pipeline def
    DSPAPI->>ArgoCtrl: Create Argo Workflow CR

    ArgoCtrl->>ArgoCtrl: Schedule workflow pods

    loop For each pipeline step
        ArgoCtrl->>DriverPod: Create driver container
        DriverPod->>MLMD: Check pipeline cache<br/>(skip if cached)
        DriverPod->>DriverPod: Resolve inputs,<br/>generate pod specs
        DriverPod->>LauncherPod: Create launcher container

        LauncherPod->>LauncherPod: Execute user code
        LauncherPod->>S3_3: Upload artifacts<br/>(HTTPS/443)
        LauncherPod->>MLMD: Publish metadata +<br/>artifact references
    end

    PersistAgent->>ArgoCtrl: Watch Argo Workflow status
    PersistAgent->>DSPAPI: Sync status back<br/>to API server

    User3->>Dashboard3: View pipeline run results
    Dashboard3->>DSPAPI: Query run status + artifacts
    Dashboard3-->>User3: Pipeline results + artifact links

%% --- Workflow 4 separator ---

sequenceDiagram
    participant User4 as Data Scientist
    participant Notebook as Jupyter Notebook
    participant CodeFlareSDK as CodeFlare SDK
    participant K8sAPI4 as K8s API Server
    participant RhodsOp4 as rhods-operator
    participant Kueue4 as Kueue
    participant KubeRay4 as KubeRay Operator
    participant CodeFlareOp4 as CodeFlare Operator
    participant RayHead as Ray Head Pod
    participant RayWorker as Ray Worker Pods
    participant TrainingOp4 as Training Operator

    Note over User4,TrainingOp4: Workflow 4: Distributed Training with Quota Management

    User4->>Notebook: Write training code
    Notebook->>CodeFlareSDK: Create RayCluster/RayJob<br/>(with Kueue local queue label)
    CodeFlareSDK->>K8sAPI4: POST RayCluster CR

    K8sAPI4->>RhodsOp4: Webhook: validate Kueue<br/>queue-name label
    RhodsOp4-->>K8sAPI4: Validated

    K8sAPI4->>Kueue4: Watch: new workload
    Kueue4->>Kueue4: Create Workload object<br/>Evaluate quota against<br/>ClusterQueue

    alt Quota available
        Kueue4->>K8sAPI4: Admit workload<br/>(set admission status)
        K8sAPI4->>KubeRay4: Watch: admitted RayCluster
        KubeRay4->>K8sAPI4: Create head + worker pods

        K8sAPI4->>CodeFlareOp4: Webhook: mutate pods
        Note over CodeFlareOp4: Inject oauth-proxy sidecar<br/>Generate mTLS certificates<br/>Create NetworkPolicies<br/>Create Route for dashboard

        RayHead->>RayWorker: Establish Ray cluster<br/>(mTLS, self-signed CA)
        Note over RayHead,RayWorker: Distributed training running
    else Quota exhausted
        Kueue4->>Kueue4: Queue workload<br/>(pending admission)
        Note over Kueue4: Workload waits for<br/>quota availability
    end

    Note over User4,TrainingOp4: Alternative: PyTorchJob / MPIJob path

    User4->>K8sAPI4: Create PyTorchJob CR
    K8sAPI4->>Kueue4: Evaluate quota
    Kueue4->>K8sAPI4: Admit workload
    K8sAPI4->>TrainingOp4: Watch: admitted PyTorchJob
    TrainingOp4->>K8sAPI4: Create launcher +<br/>worker pods<br/>(gang scheduling)

%% --- Workflow 5 separator ---

sequenceDiagram
    participant User5 as Data Scientist
    participant Dashboard5 as ODH Dashboard
    participant ModelRegAPI as Model Registry API
    participant MLMD5 as ML Metadata Backend
    participant S3_5 as S3 / OCI Storage
    participant K8sAPI5 as K8s API Server
    participant CSIInit as CSI Storage Initializer
    participant ModelRegCtrl as Model Registry Controller
    participant KServe5 as KServe

    Note over User5,KServe5: Workflow 5: Model Registry to Serving

    User5->>Dashboard5: Register model in<br/>Model Registry UI
    Dashboard5->>ModelRegAPI: POST model version<br/>(storage URI, metadata)
    ModelRegAPI->>MLMD5: Store model metadata +<br/>artifact references
    ModelRegAPI-->>Dashboard5: Model registered

    User5->>Dashboard5: Deploy model from registry
    Dashboard5->>K8sAPI5: Create InferenceService<br/>(storageUri: model-registry://...)

    K8sAPI5->>CSIInit: CSI volume mount triggered
    CSIInit->>ModelRegAPI: Resolve model-registry:// URI
    ModelRegAPI-->>CSIInit: S3 path + credentials
    CSIInit->>S3_5: Download model artifact<br/>(HTTPS/443)
    Note over CSIInit: Model available on<br/>CSI ephemeral volume

    K8sAPI5->>ModelRegCtrl: Watch: ISVC with<br/>registry labels
    ModelRegCtrl->>ModelRegAPI: Fetch model metadata
    ModelRegCtrl->>K8sAPI5: Reconcile ISVC labels<br/>(lineage tracking)

    K8sAPI5->>KServe5: Normal ISVC reconciliation<br/>(Workflow 1 continues)
